body:
i agree with @sipa. Splashscreens are somethings from the last century. A splashscreen always reminds me to a bad startup/thread design. :)
Maybe we could try getting the main-window earlier and show the block/db init there somewhere. But I would also say it's not trivial because some features in the main-window must be disabled during the init-process.
@laanwj having the big-picture: how complicate would it be? Without knowing to much from the core, is it worth to have a look at it?
